  "prompt": "What is the process to register a website as press media in India ?",
  "response": "To register a website as press media in India, follow these steps:\n\n1. Preliminary Requirements:\n- News/journalistic content website\n- Registered business entity\n- Permanent website domain\n- Regular content publication\n\n2. Registration Process:\na) Registration with Registrar of Newspapers for India (RNI)\n- Fill Form A for online registration\n- Provide website details\n- Submit necessary documents\n- Pay registration fee\n\nb) Required Documents:\n- Proof of website ownership\n- Company/business registration certificate\n- Editorial team details\n- Website content samples\n- PAN card\n- Address proof\n- Incorporation certificate\n\n3. Online Registration Procedure:\n- Visit RNI website (rni.nic.in)\n- Create user account\n- Fill online application\n- Upload supporting documents\n- Pay registration fees\n- Submit application\n\n4. State-level Additional Requirements:\n- Some states might have additional local registration procedures\n- Check specific state press registration guidelines\n\n5. Post-Registration:\n- Receive registration certificate\n- Comply with press regulations\n- Maintain content standards\n\n6. Optional: Press Council of India (PCI) registration for additional credibility\n\nNote: Specific requirements might vary, so consulting legal experts is recommended.",
